                                         CAPE TOWN - South African Airways  (SAA) on Tuesday said even with a recent government injection of R10 billion ($709 million), the struggling airline will remain under-capitalised with a negative equity position of over R9 billion, a presentation to parliament showed. The national airline has been relying on government guarantees to keep it solvent and has been cited by major rating agencies as a threat to South Africaâ€™s economy.